    public class CommonTagCompound
extends CommonTag
implements java.util.Map<java.lang.String,CommonTag>
    An NBTTagCompound wrapper which is used to map values to keys

      • removeValue

        public <T> T removeValue(java.lang.String key,
                         java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Removes the value associated with a key. This returns the value of the tag, not the tag itself. Returns null if no tag was contained.

        Possible returned types:
        List, Map, byte, boolean, short, int, long, float, double, byte[], int[], String, UUID, BlockLocation, IntVector3, other**

        ** these types are serialized from/to a stored String type.
        Parameters:
        key - to remove
        type - to cast the value to (type of value to remove)
        Returns:
        value of the tag at the key, null if not contained

      • putValue

        public <T> T putValue(java.lang.String key,
                      java.lang.Class<T> type,
                      T value)
        Sets the value of the element representing a given key. Use a data of null to remove the data at the key.

        Supported data types:
        CommonTag, NBTBase, List, Map, byte, boolean, short, int, long, float, double, byte[], int[], String, UUID, BlockLocation, IntVector3, other**

        ** these types are serialized from/to a stored String type.
        Parameters:
        key - of the element to set
        type - of value to set
        value - to assign to this key, null to remove it

      • putValue

        public void putValue(java.lang.String key,
                     java.lang.Object value)
        Sets the value of the element representing a given key. Use a data of null to remove the data at the key.

        Supported data types:
        CommonTag, NBTBase, List, Map, byte, boolean, short, int, long, float, double, byte[], int[], String, UUID*, BlockLocation*, IntVector3*, other**

        * these types do not support removing, use #removeValue(key, type) or putValue(String, Class, Object) instead
        ** these types are serialized from/to a stored String type.
        Parameters:
        key - of the element to set
        value - to assign to this key

      • getUUID

        public java.util.UUID getUUID(java.lang.String key)
        Gets an UUID value from two previously-stored keys. If the key is 'Entity' then two long values 'EntityUUIDMost' and 'EntityUUIDLeast' are read. If either of the two values are missing, null is returned instead
        Parameters:
        key - to read
        Returns:
        value at the key

      • putUUID

        public void putUUID(java.lang.String key,
                    java.util.UUID data)
        Puts an UUID value by storing it under two keys. If the key is 'Entity' then two long values 'EntityUUIDMost' and 'EntityUUIDLeast' are stored. If the data is null, the elements at the key are removed
        Parameters:
        key - to put at
        data - to put

      • getBlockLocation

        public BlockLocation getBlockLocation(java.lang.String key)
        Gets a Block Location value from previously-stored keys. If the key is 'Spawn' then the world 'SpawnWorld' and coordinates 'SpawnX', 'SpawnY' and 'SpawnZ' are read. If some of the values are missing, null is returned instead
        Parameters:
        key - to read
        Returns:
        value at the key

      • putBlockLocation

        public void putBlockLocation(java.lang.String key,
                             BlockLocation location)
        Puts a Block Location value by storing it under a world and three coordinate keys. If the key is 'Spawn', then 'SpawnWorld' and the coordinates 'SpawnX', 'SpawnY' and 'SpawnZ' are stored. If the data is null, the elements at the key are removed.
        Parameters:
        key - to put at
        location - to put
